**The Patrol Map work**

I've also dropped in the email thread on the Patrol Map. The short version is I've asked Flynn to flip the sequence on this one. SOP first, defining the operational zones, what they mean and the approvals around moving between them, with LIMSOC then configured to reflect what we've decided operationally rather than introducing the concepts.

The trigger was naming. "Primary Patrol Area" collides with the existing RWC "primary" meaning, which is about priority not capability, and putting them side by side would have confused our people. The deeper concern is that we'd have been using LIMSOC to introduce operational concepts that weren't defined first. Better to get the operational definitions right and have LIMSOC reflect them.

What I've put forward is Active Patrol Zone (over Primary), Emergency Response Zone, and Information Sharing Zone, with the RWC primary/secondary structure kept separate and documented in the SOP as priority not capability. Would love your read on the pivot, and whether that naming holds up against how you and the SDOs talk about these zones day to day.

**SME groups for the LIMSOC priorities**

Alex and I have been kicking around how we get more people engaged on the major projects without overloading the small group of us who'd otherwise hold all the input. What we've landed on is four informal SME groups, one per major project area:

- Incident Categorisation and Flow
- Call Out Systems and Capabilities
- Rostering within LIMSOC
- AI within our Incident Management Practice

These sit outside the formal governance structure. Input only, decisions stay where they are now.

Alex has come back with stakeholder coverage per group and a clear steer to go via the area leads to identify reps, rather than broadcasting an EOI. The logic is that rep support tends to equal leadership support, which keeps the SME work pointed in the same direction as our broader strategy. In practice that means you'd be the channel for SDO, SAC and ARO reps across three of the four groups (Incident Categorisation and Flow, Call Out Systems and Capabilities, AI within IM). Keen to hear your take on the approach, the group framing, and who you reckon the right reps are.

